Reasoning: The paper discusses the problem of analyzing the outage probability in cellular systems affected by cochannel interference and background noise, which is a topic related to information theory and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses wireless information-theoretic security, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses scenarios in which the connection between interference and eavesdropping can be applied, which is related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) due to its focus on wireless communication.
